{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"e9d372a9-461e-49eb-82d4-5a0f63c49840","content":"\n\nHere's the likely cause and fix for each:\n\n**1. `GoToAsync(\"productdetails\")` throws**\nThe route isn't registered. Pages not declared in the Shell XAML hierarchy must be registered explicitly:\n```csharp\n// In AppShell constructor or MauiProgram.cs\nRouting.RegisterRoute(\"productdetails\", typeof(ProductDetailsPage));\n```\nThen navigate with: `await Shell.Current.GoToAsync(\"productdetails\");`\n\n---\n\n**2. `GoToAsync(\"//products/active\")` — navigates but nothing changes**\nThe page was already created and Shell doesn't re-instantiate it. Your data-loading logic is likely only in the **constructor**. Move it to a lifecycle method that fires on every navigation:\n\n```csharp\nprotected override void OnNavigatedTo(NavigatedToEventArgs args)\n{\n    base.OnNavigatedTo(args);\n    LoadData(); // refresh here, not just in the constructor\n}\n```\n\nOr implement `IQueryAttributable` if you pass parameters.\n\n---\n\n**3. Slow startup with 12 pages**\nYou're probably using inline content instead of deferred templates. This instantiates **all 12 pages at startup**.\n\n❌ Eager (all created immediately):\n```xml\n<ShellContent Route=\"active\">\n    <local:ActivePage />\n</ShellContent>\n```\n\n✅ Deferred (created on first visit):\n```xml\n<ShellContent Route=\"active\"\n    ContentTemplate=\"{DataTemplate local:ActivePage}\" />\n```\n\nUse `ContentTemplate` with `DataTemplate` on every `ShellContent` so pages are created lazily, only when the user navigates to them.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"236b3831-50df-4006-930a-b252674968f3","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about three common .NET MAUI Shell navigation issues. These are conceptual/debugging questions — I don't need to explore a codebase. Let me answer directly from my knowledge.\n\n1. **GoToAsync(\"productdetails\") throws an exception** — The route isn't registered. In Shell, routes defined in XAML (as ShellContent/Tab/FlyoutItem) are automatically registered, but if \"productdetails\" is a page you navigate to programmatically (not declared in the Shell visual hierarchy), you must register it with `Routing.RegisterRoute(\"productdetails\", typeof(ProductDetailsPage))`.\n\n2. **GoToAsync(\"//products/active\") navigates but nothing visible changes** — The `//` prefix is an absolute route. \n\nThe page likely isn't refreshing because the route resolves to the same page already on screen, or the ShellContent isn't using `ContentTemplate` properly — if it's using `Content` directly, the page instance gets reused without re-initialization. The fix is to use `ContentTemplate` with a DataTemplate, ensure the route hierarchy matches the Shell structure, and implement `IQueryAttributable` to handle data updates when parameters change.\n\nBut wait, another possibility is that the Tab or FlyoutItem itself isn't visible in the UI — maybe `IsVisible` or `FlyoutItemIsVisible` is set to false, or the Shell items aren't structured correctly so the visual switch doesn't actually show up even though the route changed.\n\nActually, the most likely culprit is that the page content stays the same because either the ShellContent items are reusing the same page type, or the page isn't refreshing its data when navigation occurs — the fix would be implementing `IQueryAttributable` or hooking into `OnNavigatedTo` to reload the data on each navigation.\n\nThe real issue is probably a mismatch between the route hierarchy in XAML and what's being navigated to. If you have a FlyoutItem with Route=\"products\" containing a Tab with Route=\"active\" and a ShellContent with Route=\"list\", then navigating to `//products/active` would hit the Tab but not specify which ShellContent to display, making it look like nothing changed even though the navigation technically succeeded.\n\nThe fix depends on the specific problem: if the route isn't registered at all, use `Routing.RegisterRoute`; if the page loads once and doesn't refresh on subsequent navigations, hook into `OnNavigatedTo` or implement `IQueryAttributable` to reload data; and if startup is slow with many pages, switch to `ContentTemplate` for lazy loading instead of instantiating everything upfront. These are all common Shell routing gotchas in .NET MAUI.","outputTokens":1533},"id":"343f769c-c99d-48c4-8bda-21e6cff17ef6","timestamp":"2026-04-03T00:46:50.026Z","parentId":"2ae956bd-f11c-42b1-b988-ab4a5da366b3"}
